snippet.textDisplay: I can't get over how creative and original Gorillaz are, even after so many years. Even when I don't enjoy a song they've made, I can almost always respect the creative achievement it is. Gorillaz constantly push the boundaries of what I expect from them and what I expect from music generally. It's really inspiring to see people this persistently driven to do something new and interesting in an industry built off doing the exact opposite. Thanks for every piece of music and art you guys have made, you've improved my life in a real, tangible way and I'm really greatful for that. Cheers to another decade of awesome music :)

snippet.textDisplay:
I've been in a state of mind where I felt as though I was sacrificing opinion for safety. The world has creeps and weirdos alike, mad-men and scammers as well. It's really hard to know who to trust these days, now I'm seeing how all it all can be.

Your music is something, and it helps me feel better when I feel I'm nothing. The world seems to hold a bleak future, and I hope that the events of the present are just karma and not the results of some foolish person. I hope that this is the worst it could possibly get, but I doubt it. It might be a lie, for false hope possibly. Damon, you might not ever read this comment, but I hope that you continue to create. Most of my friends don't even know who Gorillaz are, and now I'm starting to think that the things I come back to might not be remembered in the coming years. I hope that doesn't happen. I forged my own chains to the past, and once in a while, I'd like to make myself think that I'm not lying to myself, but I also don't want to admit that the world can be a place where horrible things happen. I miss my childhood... Then, I didn't have to worry about the kind of stuff I worry about now.

Thank you for everything you've done. This song makes me think that my existence is not meaningless. Your other songs have been something I've grown up with, and I am really grateful that you were trying to send a message through music.

Peace.
